@BitPaine @CanadianSatoshi @Strategy People ask why MSTR should have a premium.

Maintaining a USD reserve, and a number of highly liquid capital market tools (common stock, BTC holdings, preferreds, debt) and being willing to do counter-cyclical things with those tools, is the good-optics answer to that question.

To their credit, Strategy paid off a 2029 convertible bond with the cash. They didn't just go all-aggressive; but rather they depleted the USD reserve to reduce legacy debt.

I'd argue that maintaining a strong USD reserve (and with in prior guidance, since maintaining guidance is important for investors) for the flagship STRC is more important than pre-emptive convert elimination.

Clearly though, management analyzed it and decided another way.

